On Sat, US President Joe Biden was asked if he was encouraging #Israel to delay any ground offensive into the #Gaza Strip.

In response, Biden simply said he was "talking to the Israelis".

Israel is widely expected to launch the offensive, but the timing remains unknown.

UK PM Sunak calls for all water supplies to be restored to Gaza wherever it is physically possible.

content:
OBSCURE SCARY MOVIE THREAD Entry 6: The Wolf of Snow Hollow

The Wolf of Snow Hollow starts the way you'd expect, young couple on a snowy vacation in a cabin outside a resort town, lady goes outside, _something_ eats her, standard shit.

THEN small town cops start step in and, in a marvelous left-turn, the movie starts developing character more than plot because haha THE COPS SUCK.

If, as previously established, small-town monster are either A) troubled but intrepidly up to the task or B) standard cop window-dressing ancillary to the plot and destined for mangling, the Snow Hollow cops are def central to the story but more tend toward Z) REALish small town cops dealing with unfathomable horror, i.e. they aren't very smart and generally suck at life.

A $420,000 home with the current 7.57% mortgage rate results in a monthly mortgage payment at more than $2,800.

content:
Ants are the strange members of the hymenopterans. What defines a "bee" or a "wasp" ?

Flying! Stinging! Ovipositing! Bright warning colors!

Ants looked at the main advantages of being hymenopteran and said... nah. I guess stinging is OK... (Though most ants don't sting.) ... but most of this is nothing compared to going eusocial.

Personally I think eusociality is such a huge advantage this makes sense.

But then why aren't the bees who do both more successful? Are they too specialized?

content: Biked the Sunrise road in Mt Rainier today during magical period when the road is closed to cars, but still open to bikes until the first snow. It's 14 miles up with a not-so-bad grade of 6% all the way. Great views of the mountain and so quiet without the traffic. Plus saw two bears on the road ! (but too far to get a picture). #SilentSunday #biketooter #PNW #MtRainierNP

content:
I need a little #Fedihelp from those devs in the know: Best practices on links to Fediverse accounts?

Because reasons, there are two ways to represent Fediverse handles:

1. @username@servername.tld
2. https://servername.tld/@username

The first is how a handle should display, and the latter is what you have to use if you want to link to a Fediverse account.

It's not currently possible to get @username@servername.tld to actually "work" as a link on it's own out in the wild web, is it?

I'm assuming not, so I'm also assuming that I should store the username and the servername.tld in two different fields in my database, they I can display and link them as I want, yeah?

Before I do that, I thought I'd ask to make sure there isn't a solution I should know about.

content:
So, I have been correlating my watch data and the cpap device data for about a month now. Seems that at least the Garmin watches track "restless moments" while asleep that, when divided by the number of hours slept, roughly correlate within a few points to my cpap data.

So for folks who wear their watches while sleeping, that's a good metric to keep an eye on. It can warn you of trouble ahead.

content: Last week @ambulephabus and I crossed 16 years since our 1st date, which we call our “meetiversary”—we didn’t take any photos that night in 2007, but here are 2 from that year’s Halloween and Thanksgiving. It’s weird to feel both like it hasn’t been that long and like being with him is all I’ve known. But these last 18 months, as we’ve both crossed 40, it’s been particularly special. I’m honestly amazed at the depth and breadth of new experiences we’ve had and I am here for it. I love you, Bubb.

Ahhh, old school Portland. 😌

I took him to a bar called The Sapphire Hotel, which I delighted in knowing was a former brothel. It was delightfully romantic decor with good cocktails and decent food. But I do remember it pouring down rain with cold blasts of wind chilling us every time the door opened.

content:
You can reduce car use in simple ways, but you cannot solve the problem with cars without looking at a web of systemic oppressions that are forcing even some people who want to go car-free to hang onto one.

It's hard to take some simplistic advocacy seriously when it's often coming from white men with jobs that pay >$100,000/yr. who have never really encountered these things except as a footnote on a white paper.

content:
I always find it irritating to see photos or videos of large satellite dishes with representations of video or other data as a narrow beam traveling directly to or from the feed horn at the focal point. Even the BBC News has done this with their top-of-hour countdown sequences and such.

In reality, the data is transmitted to or received from the entire surface of the dish.

No wonder science education is falling apart.

content:
This week's #SixOnSaturday is inspired by all the lovely autumn photos in my timeline. I'm calling it "Looking for Fall."

Bc it's 91°F today. In October.

(I wish I was joking.)

My garden is blazing hot, ridiculously green & not an autumn vibe in sight. This is the best I could find. 😂

(**Editing to add that I don't want to sound ungrateful - I'm thankful for the rain & that my garden is lovely & green. My brain just wants to shift into Fall weather - snuggly sweaters & cool crisp air. And yeah...that's just not happening lol)

#gardening #TexasGarden #Zone9a

21/#31nightsofhalloween #MicrosCreepy
Naegleria are crawling amoebae most of the time, but when stressed, they can grow two flagella (same structure as sperm tails) to swim away. This cell was stained for microtubules, which form flagella and an extensive network in the cell body beneath the plasma membrane.

Okay, another pile of fixes later including an ALSA kernel core fix (because of course), speakers are finally stable across suspend/resume even while playing audio.

Using a just-released PipeWire Fedora package too. Now we just need to wrap up our own packaging, add the missing speaker profiles and improve the DSP configs, fix up the rest of the DTs with the regulator thing, add the remaining models to the macaudio driver, merge the kernel branch with all this, fix a thing in the UCMs that came out of debugging the jack mic gain with @1ace after XDC... getting there.

content:
Got a message from my JVP chapter here in North NJ:

We are distressed and saddened to have to contact you at this late date to inform you of the cancellation of NNJ JVP's event: "An Open Conversation: An opportunity to share your responses to the current situation in Israel/Palestine" scheduled for this Sunday, October 22, 2023 at 1:30-3:30 pm at the Unitarian Universalist Congregation at Montclair (UUCM). The event was co-sponsored and endorsed by a wide variety of religious and community organizations
Yesterday, the minister of the UUCM called and emailed us to rescind our rental contract, forcing cancellation of the event. The Executive Committee of the church's Board stated, without any further explanation, they had received complaints about our event and that JVP did not share the church's values nor "cohere" with its mission. We are puzzled by the reference to the values and mission we apparently do not share. It also appears that the church fears controversy.
While civilian deaths mount by the minute in the Israel/Hamas war, People of faith should have moral courage and stand up for peace, justice, and freedom for ALL in Israel/Palestine.
We are in shock that a UU church won't allow JVP and all people of good conscience to express moral concern at their church for civilians in harm's way and to discuss their reactions to the events in Israel/Gaza. Notwithstanding, we intend to reschedule this event as soon as possible.
I think I remember a song about cowards flinching

content:
We had a guest visit last night in need of some care.

His entire backend was covered in prickers and cactus needles, so my husband and I worked to get them all out and cleaned up his cuts.

He wasn't any of our neighbor's dogs, so we fed him and decided to get him checked for a chip this morning.

Getting him to the vet was a venture, as I don't think he has ever been walked on a leash before.

I ended up carrying him, as that was the easiest way to get him in and out of the car and at the vet.

Alas, he did not have a chip, so we are trying other methods to find his humans.

If we don't find them, we will take care of him until either we find someone for him, or he just gets absorbed into the pack.

A breadboard is a piece of modular circuitry, commonly used to prototype electronic systems before moving to Printed Circuit Boards (PCBs).

A cheese plate is a piece of modular camera equipment, containing various 1/4” and 3/8” holes which various attachments can be screwed into.

Both pieces of modular equipment sound tasty, but could conceivably also be combined. Hence the double entendre.

content:
I'm not a fan of dueling games, but Unmatched isn't bad. The first few times I played, I switched characters every time and didn't get to know their cards before playing. Big mistake.

This month, I played three times as Medusa. By today's third play, I knew how to use my advantages and manage my hand.

Sinbad and Medusa were both still standing when we defeated Angel and Willow. It was all but over after I played a lucky Gaze of Stone against the defenseless Willow.

#BoardGamesAtoZ #BoardGames

content:
I keep looking at Ghost and thinking *it’s so close*, but its approach to extensibility I think puts you in a very similar trap to Craft, which is that you ultimately get stuck paying for a bunch of extra stuff just to keep your site online and active.

The difference is that Ghost offloads all that stuff to third parties like Zapier whereas Craft has you paying for plugins every year.

content:
one thought if you have food and rent covered for you, you're not busy with the business of survival.

it somewhat resembles childhood, because your parents are taking care of that part.

the next human need is belonging and love. when a child doesn't have that, we call it parental neglect.

and i guess if an adult doesn't have it, that's self-neglect.

i think this happens to neurodivergent people a lot. there are emotional needs, but you're dysfunctional, so you don't know how to satisfy them, and then you get depressed.

content:
”‘rugged individualism’… is only a masked attempt to repress and defeat the individual and his individuality. So-called Individualism is the social and economic laissez-faire: the exploitation of the masses by the [ruling] classes by means of legal trickery, spiritual debasement and systematic indoctrination of the servile spirit … That corrupt and perverse ‘individualism’ is the straitjacket of individuality .. [It] has inevitably resulted in the greatest modern slavery, the crassest class distinctions driving millions to the breadline. ‘Rugged individualism’ has meant all the ‘individualism’ for the masters, while the people are regimented into a slave caste to serve a handful of self-seeking ‘supermen.’”

- Emma Goldman

Je viens de finir Tunic (pour être précis, pour celles et ceux qui savent, j'ai fini A+B+10f+4s, et je vais m'arrêter là).

Je sais que ce jeu indépendant est sorti y'a déjà un an et demi, mais quelle claque. Une équipe qui se compte sur les doigts de deux mains qui fait un jeu qui m'a retourné le cerveau pendant 15+ heures, un bonbon.

Il a même réussi à me faire sortir un papier et un crayon pour prendre des notes (tard dans le jeu) 👌

Je vous le recommande chaudement.

https://store.steampowered.com/app/553420/TUNIC/

I've also been told that it's not my place to say what the Israeli government should and shouldn't do. That if I don't personally have a solution, I can't decry depriving millions of people of food/water/electricity.

But it 100% is my place to speak to my own government (and encourage my compatriots to do the same) against providing weapons and other support to a government that has declared its plans that amount to collective punishment.

3/

content:
Chronicling my journey toward creating my first #flower garden (aka. “Big Dreams, Zero Skills”)

Day 1:

Not a great start today. While I was amassing and organizing materials in the yard, a wasp landed on my shoulder and I was later divebombed by a HUGE bug. They were harmless, but it freaked me out (I HATE creepy crawlies). So I changed my plans and decided to create a smaller plot nearer to my patio where I felt “safer” instead (it’s stupid, I know).

1/2

#Gardening #Garden

Data: NCHS, Census. Accidents figure for 2022 is provisional (not final). 

[ beadsland on Ko-fi ]

Dashed lines for annual data for years 2015 through 2021 for causes liver disease & self-harm; through 2022 for accidents (unintentional injuries). Dotted lines indicate trendlines for Jan 2020 forward, for each cause category.

Legend:

* Accidents (unintentional injuries) (+45K more annual deaths vs. 2019)
* Chronic liver disease and cirrhosis (+12.2K)
* Intentional self-harm (suicide) (+0.7K)
* Projected U.S. population

Caption:

Accidents (unintentional injuries) have returned to their pre-pandemic standing as third leading cause of death in the United States. While deaths for which covid-19 was the attributed underlying cause of death were, indeed, down from prior two calendar years, 2022 saw many more deadly accidents than would have been predicted based on 2015-2019 trendline. Were it not for this sustained spike in accidental deaths, covid would have retained third place.

Chronic liver disease and cirrhosis saw a near identical jump in relative mortality over the first two years of the pandemic. As of yet, only provisional figures for 2022’s top four causes of death are available. (Final “statistics”—if not “data”—for all causes might be available end of this year.)

новость: ученые выяснили, как кошки мурчат (=^･ω･^=)

первоисточник: «мы пропустили теплый влажный воздух через восемь извлеченных из кошек гортаней...»

Ahem. Надеюсь, они у вас хотя бы строили, вы собрали из них полную октаву и что-нибудь на них исполнили.

(Пишут также: «Larynx stability was maintained with an adjustable plastic support structure (using LEGO blocks, Billund, Denmark)». Мммм. Кажется, начинаю понимать, как в своих статьях лучше сформулировать «подложили две книжки и брошюру» и «прилепили на пластилин и подстраховали изолентой»).

В общем, установлено, что кошачья гортань может мурчать без кошачьего мозга и остальной кошки, в остальном всё, как всегда, «остаётся недостаточно изученным», пока не найдут способ поддержания хорошего настроения живой кошки во время научного исследования: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.cub.2023.09.014

content:
After our final long hike in Gatlinburg, we were struggling to find a good place to eat lunch this morning.

We were sick of the chain stuff, so we tried to find something local. The first place we went made it clear they had no room for us. The second didn’t take card, sadly.

But we eventually found a very legit BBQ place, in the middle of friggin’ nowhere, that a preacher opened up after a wildfire. It was, in a phrase, game-changing.

content:
I've proposed a standard for grouping cached responses together, so you can do things like invalidate them together.

Various caches already do this (including many CDNs), but it's all over the map.

If you're a HTTP person and this sounds like a good idea to you, please support the call for adoption:
https://www.w3.org/mid/AF939A2D-A7BC-4950-8A03-3567F58403C9@apple.com

there was a discussion in this ADHD chatroom about neurodivergence and polyamory.

someone asked if #neurodivergent people are more likely to be polyamorous.

there came an objection to it: "no, actually, that's a coping strategy, because people aren't interested in having serious relationships with them."

content:
#南宋行暮 罢黜朱熹，揭开了庆元党禁的序幕。庆元党禁是统治阶级内部的党争，但却以道学之禁为其主要内容和外在形式，把朋党之争和道学之争错综复杂地搅和在一起。故而有必要对道学之争做一简单的回溯，才能把握党争为何以学禁为主题和外衣。
面对唐宋之际深刻的社会变动，传统的旧儒学日渐显得苍白无力。自仁宗时代起，周敦颐、张载、邵雍、程颢、程颐等各自著书立说，聚徒讲学，形成了宋代新儒学流派纷呈的局面。二程兄弟，尤其程颐，活动年代最迟，授业弟子最多，思想体系最为精致，始以道学为天下倡。宋室南渡，二程之学蔚为大宗，经杨时、罗从彦、李侗三传，到李侗弟子朱熹手中，遂集北宋以来理学之大成，标志着程朱理学的最终完成。朱熹因思想博大精深，人格光风霁月，弟子遍及海内，学说风行一时，自然而然成为孝宗以后南宋思想界的一面旗帜。有一种偏见认为，朱熹等理学家只是空谈性命道德。其实，他们倒不是专尚空谈的：首先，他们身体力行自己提出的道德性命之学；其次，他们也要求包括君王在内，人人都这样去做，格物致知，居敬穷理，小则修身齐家，大则治国平天下，内圣的功夫便能翻出外王的世界。理学家不仅仅独善其身，还是要兼济天下的。

content:
#南宋行暮 不过，中国学术思想史上有一种倾向，即强调门户之见、道统之说，总认为只有自己的学说为谠言正论，其他思想是异端邪说，总希望天下只有自家一说的声音。朱熹理学也未能克服这一倾向。陈亮曾为道学中人画像：
因吾眼之偶开，便以为得不传之绝学。三三两两，附耳而语，有同告密；画界而立，一似结坛。尽绝一世之人于门外。
他们不愿意承认人心不同，见解自异，即便圣人不能绳律天下之人，尽弃己学而独尊道学；而是以道统自任，以严师自居，别白是否，毫不宽容。
以这种态度去治学，至多引起理学不同派别之间的“道问学”与“尊德性”的讨论，程朱学派和经世学派之间的“王霸义利”的争辩。但随着持这种门户之见的理学家进入官僚圈的人数日渐增多，问题就超出了思想学术的界限，他们以门户与道统为抑扬品题的标尺，既然有揄扬，当然也有贬抑，随着品题既众，致使疑怨丛生，主观上全出于至公，形迹上已涉及朋党。尽管自我标榜“君子同而不当”，反倒更容易刺激那批门户、道统之外官宦们的朋党情绪。只要一有适当的政治火星，朋党之争就会被点燃。

content: #南宋行暮 不仅如此，中国学术思想史上还有一种通病：某种学说一旦成为显学，一哄而起的赶时髦风尚总使其滑向庸俗化和形式化的泥淖。正如周密所描述，在道学传播中，“有一种浅陋之士，自视无堪以为进取之地，辄亦自附于道学之名。褒衣博带，危坐阔步。或抄节语录以资高谈，或闭眉合眼号为默识。而叩击其所学，则于古今无所闻知；考验其所行，则于义利无所分别”。除去这类浅薄无知者，晚宋俞文豹则揭露了那些别具用心者：“有一等赝儒，素以钻刺为生，见时尚道学，旋取《近思录》《性学源流》等书剽窃其语，置牙颊间，以诳惑人听。外示雍容，内实急于进取，口谈道学，心实巧于逢迎。”[7]惟其如此，便容易让小人找到借口指其为伪学之名，而使君子受到连累而有玉石俱焚之祸。

content: #南宋行暮 宋代朋党之争，自北宋初年开始，几乎从未消歇过，但朋党之争与道学之争错综纠葛则集中在高、孝、光、宁时期。其时正是程朱理学骎骎乎由话语权之争向独尊之学迈进的时期。理学家及道学依附者在官僚层中所占比例激增，他们执道学门户之见，自视甚高而责人太苛；而那些被排在道学门户之外被责的官僚们，因道学尚未被定为独尊的官学，还有被议论指摘的可能性，便在发动朋党之争的同时，对政敌所主张的道学也一并实施攻击，以便从根本上摧毁政敌。因此，在道学已成显学却未成官学的这一时期，朋党之争往往以道学与非道学之争为其主要内容和外在形式，就是绝非偶然的了。理宗以后以迄明清，因理学已定于一尊，尽管朋党之争仍是君主官僚体制难以克服的痼疾，与道学之争却脱了钩。

content:
"Ode to Spot" was an ode composed by Data in 2369, addressed to his pet cat, Spot. (TNG: "Schisms")

Felis catus is your taxonomic nomenclature,
An endothermic quadruped, carnivorous by nature;
Your visual, olfactory, and auditory senses
Contribute to your hunting skills and natural defenses.

I find myself intrigued by your subvocal oscillations,
A singular development of cat communications
That obviates your basic hedonistic predilection
For a rhythmic stroking of your fur to demonstrate affection.

A tail is quite essential for your acrobatic talents;
You would not be so agile if you lacked its counterbalance.
And when not being utilized to aid in locomotion,
It often serves to illustrate the state of your emotion.

O Spot, the complex levels of behavior you display
Connote a fairly well-developed cognitive array.
And though you are not sentient, Spot, and do not comprehend,
I nonetheless consider you a true and valued friend.

https://youtu.be/SySZdvsFYt4?feature=shared

#StarTrekTNG #StarTrek #CatsOfMastodon

#Autism? A state of being. Not an identity group.

No code of conduct. No approved language. No secret handshake.

You don't need anyone's approval to be #autistic.

It's not like they can kick you out. Just... not let you sit at their lunch table.

You're used to that.

Do you.

It's the healthy demand avoidance side of me speaking. I tend to get bitchy around demands for conformity.

Like I need to adopt a new mask. At my age.

#ActuallyAutistic
@actuallyautistic

content:
Apparently this place, which is miles away from the next-closest business, is newly famous. About a year ago, Dolly Parton, who grew up right nearby, took Jimmy Fallon to this place.

But don’t let that selling point convince you it is anything more than a low-key experience. It was just a stand, a couple of picnic tables, and a little room where you could eat BBQ.

If you ever find yourself in the Smoky Mountains, Preachers Smokehouse BBQ is the real deal.

content:
The top cop is the late great Robert Forster, who, like Robert Forster at time of filming, is ready to retire and come ON with this monster shit! Which leaves his son (the movie's writer and director Jim Cummings) the sort of lead guy, in spite of Ricki Lindholme (YAY) being the only arguably competent cop in the gaggle. It's a good hook, though, because he's a posturing twat and the other cops hate him.

Props to Cumimngs, he shoots this all like a pretty straight horror movie - like's it's not Keystone Buffy or somesuch - with his own character undergoing crescendo of incompetent mania breaking through his normal hapless deadpan, occasionally interrupted by aghast shrieks at the inevitable disemboweled corpses.

Also, just one dialogue tidbit from the library scene: "Hey, Ray, quick librarian note? A police officer asks you to take out all the spooky books in the library, maybe don't sneak up on him."

It feels like Cummings' starting premise was "What if genuinely shitty cops with bad coping skills had to deal with unfathomable horror shit WAY beyond their capacities" and I, for one, consider this an admirable experiment in declicheing the genre. 12/5 stars.
